{
  "texts": [
    "I will argue that both approaches to transparency have shortcomings: process-based accounts fail to show whether the system that results from the described development process meets (ethical) standards because the behaviour of (machine-learning) systems is hard to predict based purely on the steps taken by developers.",
    "On the other hand, current outcome-based accounts take too narrow a view of AI systems and miss parts of the process that have been shown to be crucial to perceptions of legitimacy.",
    "Instead, I'll argue in Sect.",
    "\"Value-based transparency\" that an approach based on the whole range of values we want to realise in an AI system, effectively extending current outcome-based approaches, manages to handle these issues nicely and fits with current best practices on the realisation of responsible AI.",
    "What kind of transparency do we need?"
  ]
}